he user mentioned not running it directly, but I'm thinking about adjusting long lines over 120 characters — maybe looking at a max of 112 or 120. There's a concern about top-level non-public classes in the same file, particularly since only the top-level test class is public. Plus, there's an issue with `ClassDesc.of(PACKAGE_NAME, simpleName)` if the simple name isn't valid. I’m also pondering how native images handle package-private top-level fixtures and their static reachability.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Native Image and Class Loading**\\n\\nI’m considering how the class hierarchy resolver might be using `cl.getSuperclass()` along with `referenceClassDesc` from the class object, and how the Native Image handle reflection metadata for this. I’m concerned about whether `Class.forName` really calls `Java ClassLoader.loadClass` in native images, given that support for custom class loading seems limited. If the class is in the image heap, it might directly call `loader.loadClass`. I need to think through how tests with custom class loaders could fail, as dynamic loading isn't supported in Native Image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Native Image ClassLoader Behavior**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether a native image allows `ClassLoader.loadClass` on the application class loader, and if a custom `ClassLoader.loadClass` will run. There’s something called `ClassLoaderSupport` which might be fine. However, I’m concerned about the exact count not happening if `Class.forName` is intrinsified. If the name and loader aren’t constant, it could still execute and call `Class.forName`. In a native image, dynamic usage of `Class.forName` with non-constant names needs configuration; perhaps I should just avoid the custom loader altogether.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_W4XSL2auSK6yOpo1LmDD51Xn|fc_00630b6c0726f41d0169f409ae20e88196aaa7e20c09202909", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.smallrye.classfile/jdk-classfile-backport/26/src/test/java/io_smallrye_classfile/jdk_classfile_backport/ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous3Test.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.constant.ClassDesc;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.constant.ClassDesc;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void resolvesHierarchyInformationByLoadingClassesThroughProvidedClassLoader() {\n        TrackingClassLoader loader = new TrackingClassLoader();\n        ClassHierarchyResolver resolver = ClassHierarchyResolver.ofClassLoading(loader);\n\n        ClassHierarchyInfo childInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(CHILD_CLASS_NAME));\n        ClassHierarchyInfo interfaceInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME));\n\n        assertThat(childInfo).isEqualTo(ClassHierarchyInfo.ofClass(testClassDesc(PARENT_CLASS_NAME)));\n        assertThat(interfaceInfo).isEqualTo(ClassHierarchyInfo.ofInterface());\n        assertThat(loader.loadAttempts(binaryName(CHILD_CLASS_NAME))).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(loader.loadAttempts(binaryName(INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME))).isEqualTo(1);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void returnsNullWhenProvidedClassLoaderCannotFindClass() {\n        TrackingClassLoader loader = new TrackingClassLoader();\n        ClassHierarchyResolver resolver = ClassHierarchyResolver.ofClassLoading(loader);\n\n        ClassHierarchyInfo missingInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(MISSING_CLASS_NAME));\n\n        assertThat(missingInfo).isNull();\n        assertThat(loader.loadAttempts(binaryName(MISSING_CLASS_NAME))).isEqualTo(1);\n    }\n", "newText": "    void resolvesHierarchyInformationByLoadingClassesThroughProvidedClassLoader() {\n        ClassLoader loader = ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous3Test.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassHierarchyResolver resolver = ClassHierarchyResolver.ofClassLoading(loader);\n\n        ClassHierarchyInfo childInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(CHILD_CLASS_NAME));\n        ClassHierarchyInfo interfaceInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME));\n\n        assertThat(childInfo).isEqualTo(ClassHierarchyInfo.ofClass(testClassDesc(PARENT_CLASS_NAME)));\n        assertThat(interfaceInfo).isEqualTo(ClassHierarchyInfo.ofInterface());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void returnsNullWhenProvidedClassLoaderCannotFindClass() {\n        ClassLoader loader = ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous3Test.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassHierarchyResolver resolver = ClassHierarchyResolver.ofClassLoading(loader);\n\n        ClassHierarchyInfo missingInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(testClassDesc(MISSING_CLASS_NAME));\n\n        assertThat(missingInfo).isNull();\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "\n    private static String binaryName(String simpleName) {\n        return PACKAGE_NAME + \".\" + simpleName;\n    }\n\n    private static final class TrackingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final Map<String, Integer> loadAttemptsByName = new HashMap<>();\n\n        private TrackingClassLoader() {\n            super(ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous3Test.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (name.startsWith(PACKAGE_NAME + \".ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous3\")) {\n                loadAttemptsByName.merge(name, 1, Integer::sum);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n        }\n\n        private int loadAttempts(String binaryName) {\n            return loadAttemptsByName.getOrDefault(binaryName, 0);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": ""}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 951, "output": 2538, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19361, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777600913616, "responseId": "resp_00630b6c0726f41d0169f40991f61c8196a99423bbbe80d09f"}}
